  "finger_focus": "Shift + 1 = !, Shift + / = ?",
  "tips": [
    {
      "type": "lead",
      "text": "The period and comma keep order. Now for the marks that carry tone - the exclamation point and the question mark. One raises the voice, the other turns the sentence over to the reader. Both ride a Shift, so this lesson is as much about the two-finger combo as the marks themselves."
    },
    {
      "type": "drop",
      "text": "The exclamation point is Shift + 1: hold Shift with your right pinky, strike 1 with your left pinky. The question mark is Shift + / : hold Shift with your left pinky, strike / (next to the right Shift) with your right pinky. The rule is simple - the Shift comes from the hand opposite the key."
    },
    {
      "type": "callout",
      "icon": "⌨️",
      "title": "Hold Shift, don't stab it",
      "text": "Press Shift a beat early and keep it down while the other finger taps. A smooth hold beats a quick jab every time - jabbing is how you end up with a stray 1 or a lone slash in your copy."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "! ! ! ! ! ! ! ! ! ! ! ! ! ! !",
      "finger": "pink",
      "title": "The exclamation point",
      "hint": "Right pinky holds Shift, left pinky taps 1. Hold, tap, release."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ?",
      "finger": "pink",
      "title": "The question mark",
      "hint": "Left pinky holds Shift, right pinky taps the slash. Smooth, not sharp."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "Both marks in hand. Now use them where they belong - a question asks, an exclamation insists. Read each sentence, decide which mark closes it, and type it through. Space follows the mark, same as before."
    },
    {
      "type": "pullquote",
      "text": "An exclamation point is salt: a little sharpens the line, too much spoils the dish.",
      "by": "Eleanor Hayes, editor"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "really! is that true? yes! when did you know? right now! how amazing! are you sure?",
      "finger": "green",
      "title": "Tone in sentences",
      "hint": "Pick the right mark for each line. Hold Shift smoothly, one space after."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "Steps done? Open the trainer below and take one clean run at the full lesson text. That run saves your progress and unlocks the next lesson."
    }
